{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e8180290-aee8-4006-9a45-07a38e090881","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing a .NET crash dump. None of my specialized skills cover dump **analysis** (only collection), but here's how to proceed:\n\n### Recommended Tools\n\n**`dotnet-dump analyze`** (Linux/Windows — best for managed .NET):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file>.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `pe` | Print last exception (start here!) |\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM crashes) |\n\n**`lldb` + SOS** (Linux) or **WinDbg** (Windows) for deeper native + managed analysis.\n\n### Suggested Workflow\n1. **`pe`** — check if there's an unhandled exception\n2. **`clrthreads`** — find the faulting thread\n3. **`clrstack`** on the faulting thread — see where it crashed\n4. **`dso`** — inspect objects on the stack for clues\n\nIf you upload or place the `.dmp` file in this directory, I can run `dotnet-dump analyze` interactively and walk through these steps with you. Want to try that?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"331824ef-b08f-4595-bb9e-2d8c94a44545","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me look at the available skills to see if any are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files\n\n\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs\n\nNone of these skills are designed for analyzing dump files. Since we're on Linux, I should guide the user on using `dotnet-dump analyze` directly to examine the crash dump and identify what caused the failure.","outputTokens":616,"requestId":"7640:2D289A:E65B2C:10E11A3:69FE93A4"},"id":"30456af1-1d29-47eb-82ec-3bb8aee41df7","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:53:56.762Z","parentId":"9b02bc04-3fca-4995-af6a-9409c220786e"}
